<XMLDocContent PageName="cobalt.graphics.IRenderPassNode.RemoveAttachmentClearData" Title="RemoveAttachmentClearData method" xmlns="http://www.cobaltrenderer.com/schema/XMLDocSchema.xsd">
  <Paragraph>
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.Welcome">Home</PageRef> ->
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.IRenderPassNode">IRenderPassNode</PageRef> ->
    RemoveAttachmentClearData
  </Paragraph>
  <Section Title="Description">
    <Paragraph>
      The <TypeRef>RemoveAttachmentClearData</TypeRef> method removes any previously defined attachment clear operation
      for the specified framebuffer target, which has been defined for this render pass using the
      <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.IRenderPassNode.SetAttachmentClearData">SetAttachmentClearData</PageRef> method.
    </Paragraph>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="Usage">
    <Code Language="C++"><![CDATA[void RemoveAttachmentClearData(IFrameBuffer::AttachmentType type, size_t index);]]></Code>
    <SubSection Title="Argument list">
      <ArgumentList>
        <ArgumentListEntry Type="IFrameBuffer::AttachmentType!cobalt.graphics.IFrameBuffer.AttachmentType" Name="type">
          The type of the target framebuffer attachment
        </ArgumentListEntry>
        <ArgumentListEntry Type="size_t" Name="index">
          The index of the target framebuffer attachment within the selected attachment type
        </ArgumentListEntry>
      </ArgumentList>
    </SubSection>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="See also">
    <PageRefList>
      <PageRefListEntry PageName="cobalt.graphics.IRenderPassNode">IRenderPassNode</PageRefListEntry>
      <PageRefListEntry PageName="cobalt.graphics.IFrameBuffer">IFrameBuffer</PageRefListEntry>
    </PageRefList>
  </Section>
</XMLDocContent>
